The course deals with the research areas of lexicology and with lexicological analysis in a broader context. An overview of the content and form of the word elements is provided. Students learn to describe and analyze paradigmatic relations between words (synonymy, antonymy, hyponymy), as well as examine the syntagmatic relationships and their manifestations (collocations, valence, etc.).Objectives/eesmärkid:  This course provides a basic understanding of the structure of Danish vocabulary, word formation methods, the meaning changes, and paradigmatic-syntactic relationships. It also provides an overview of the different vocabulary and linguistic analysis methods of investigation and tries to apply them in practice.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course, the student: - names basic terminology in Danish lexicology and explains the terms by giving examples; - describes and analyses word formation methods, changes in meaning, paradigmatic and syntagmatic relations between words with the help of dictionaries; - explains collocational differences between words, chooses words fitting for the context and explains their choices; names the most prominent methods in vocabulary research and linguistic analysis.
